Found three actionable issues in trail 8 (`bd230b4`, checkpoint `fa3c8337b5a4`):

1. **[P2] TSX masking breaks valid runtime imports.** [parser.go](/Users/thomi/Projects/entire-graph/internal/sem/parser.go:458)

   `typeof import(resolveSpecifier())` is valid runtime TypeScript, but the regex stops at the inner `)` and masks it into:

   ```ts
   return any                             )
   ```

   This produces `E_PARSE_ERROR`. It becomes a regression because this patch newly applies the common mask to `.tsx`. Restrict the rewrite to actual import-type syntax, preferably with syntax-aware matching or at least a quoted module specifier.

2. **[P2] The DROP-list mask matches inside SQL strings.** [parser.go](/Users/thomi/Projects/entire-graph/internal/sem/parser.go:5080)

   Given valid SQL such as:

   ```sql
   CREATE TABLE templates (
     body text DEFAULT 'DROP TABLE a, b'
   );
   CREATE TABLE survivor (id int);
   ```

   the pattern begins inside the string and consumes through the statement semicolon, removing the closing quote and parenthesis. The result reports `E_PARSE_ERROR` and loses both table entities. Statement masks need a search view with quoted strings blanked, or a lexical statement-start check.

3. **[P2] Multi-name DROP support excludes valid common forms.** [parser.go](/Users/thomi/Projects/entire-graph/internal/sem/parser.go:5078)

   `DROP TYPE IF EXISTS mood, status;` and `DROP MATERIALIZED VIEW IF EXISTS a, b;` still produce parse errors. Other omitted list-capable kinds include foreign tables, collations, and statistics. The new mask currently covers only seven object kinds despite describing general multi-name DROP handling.

The committed suite still passes: `mise run test:ci` and `mise run vet` both succeeded. I reproduced the findings with temporary regression probes and removed them; the worktree is clean.

::code-comment{title="[P2] Runtime import corrupted by type mask" body="This regex also matches valid runtime expressions such as `typeof import(resolveSpecifier())`. Because it stops at the first closing parenthesis, the mask leaves a stray `)` and introduces an E_PARSE_ERROR in TSX files. Restrict matching to genuine import-type syntax, ideally using a syntax-aware scanner or at least a quoted module specifier." file="/Users/thomi/Projects/entire-graph/internal/sem/parser.go" start=458 priority=2}

::code-comment{title="[P2] DROP text in strings corrupts DDL" body="The pattern runs against a view that removes comments and dollar-quoted bodies but retains ordinary string literals. A string containing `DROP TABLE a, b` can therefore start a match that consumes the enclosing statement terminator, removing its closing quote/parenthesis and causing E_PARSE_ERROR plus missing later entities." file="/Users/thomi/Projects/entire-graph/internal/sem/parser.go" start=5080 priority=2}

::code-comment{title="[P2] Multi-name DROP coverage is incomplete" body="Valid list-capable forms such as `DROP TYPE IF EXISTS mood, status` and `DROP MATERIALIZED VIEW IF EXISTS a, b` remain unmasked and still produce parse errors. Extend the object-kind handling beyond the currently enumerated subset." file="/Users/thomi/Projects/entire-graph/internal/sem/parser.go" start=5078 end=5080 priority=2}

